<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-79-0882 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents a brief historical review of developments in railtechnology to the present and then goes on to discuss current developments.Competition from other transport modes has necessitated the improvedefficiency and productivity of rail transport, which in turn has ledto a number of new technological developments. Some of these developmentsare identified and include: lightweight aluminium freight cars, self-steeringtrucks, improved locomotive wheel slip systems, and automated communicationsand control systems.</TEXT></DOC>